<title>BOTSWANA: Bank of Botswana cuts bank rate half a point.</title>
<headline>Bank of Botswana cuts bank rate half a point.</headline>
<dateline>GABORONE 1997-03-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Bank of Botswana announced to commercial banks on Saturday that it had cut the bank rate half a point to 12.5 percent.</p>
<p>Managing director of Barclays Botswana, Charles Middleton, told Reuters he expected commcercial banks would review their prime rates on Tuesday, when the Bank of Botswana will release 540 million pula of Bank of Botswana Certificates in two tranches of three month and 12-month paper.</p>
</text>
